 :tx/rationale "Create task: C9-STEER-1v2: Implement CLI_COHERENCE_SPEC.md §4 output templates for observe subcommands. PROBLEM: observe list/search/show/recent produce ad-hoc output that violates INV-CLI-003 (output shape consistency). The agent-mode output is a one-line receipt, not a steering vector. THEORY: CLI_COHERENCE_SPEC.md §4 defines four templates: ListOutput (count + table + steering), DetailOutput (id/status/body/relations + steering), SearchOutput (query + ranked list + steering), CreateOutput (id + type info + 3-component steering). Each template appends a SteeringVector: concept_membership + structural_gap + question. APPROACH: (1) In run_list: render ListOutput — summary line (count + group count), then per-concept rows (name + member count + developmental stage per Piaget §3: <20=sensorimotor, 20-50=concrete, >50=formal), then SteeringVector. Default ≤10 lines (INV-CLI-006). (2) In run_search: render SearchOutput — 'search query: N results', then top 5 ranked rows with [score] [concept] body, then SteeringVector. (3) In run_show: render DetailOutput — entity id + type + attributes table + relations, then SteeringVector. (4) In run_recent: render ListOutput variant — N most recent with [category, confidence] [concept] body, then SteeringVector. (5) AgentOutput must contain the SAME template, compressed — context=scope, content=top rows + gap, footer=question+command. The agent gets a distilled steering vector, not a receipt. ACCEPTANCE: (A) All 4 subcommands match their §4 template. (B) Agent-mode output contains concept names (not just counts). (C) Default output ≤10 lines for list (INV-CLI-006). (D) SteeringVector has all 3 components (not just question). (E) JSON output has steering_question + concept_membership + structural_gap keys. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs"
